WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.930 --> 00:00:05.440
Aren't those...

2
00:00:05.870 --> 00:00:08.837
the Gate's magic circle
that we saw on the 11th floor?

3
00:00:08.920 --> 00:00:10.160
Oh no!

4
00:00:15.540 --> 00:00:17.457
Come here!
- Aren't those Dinoboros?!

5
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.790
Why are the monsters from
deeper floors on the surface?

6
00:00:22.710 --> 00:00:24.277
CLAIRIE SERAH
Rodge! I'll bring out the walls!

7
00:00:24.360 --> 00:00:25.377
CLAIRIE SERAH
Hurry up with the incantation!

8
00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:26.757
FIRE FACTION. RODGE HOLLAND
I'm counting on you!

9
00:00:26.840 --> 00:00:27.217
FIRE FACTION. RODGE HOLLAND
Ready to intercept them!

10
00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:28.500
Ready to intercept them!

11
00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:40.040
Keridos Gardinas!

12
00:00:47.530 --> 00:00:48.817
Start the incantation!

13
00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:51.980
Clairie's Guardians
will act as vanguards!

14
00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:54.860
Wipe them out!

15
00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:57.320
Blade Rachel!

16
00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:04.709
What's with that number of Guardians?

17
00:01:05.610 --> 00:01:08.050
The enemy's ambush
was crushed in an instant.

18
00:01:08.350 --> 00:01:09.800
So this is...

19
00:01:10.370 --> 00:01:12.800
The High Mages of the Tower.

20
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.567
To think anyone would dare desecrate
the capital of the Magia Vander...

21
00:01:17.650 --> 00:01:19.350
Fools.

22
00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:21.857
Trace the source of the magic circles!

23
00:01:21.940 --> 00:01:24.527
The culprit responsible for sending
the monsters is out there!

24
00:01:24.610 --> 00:01:26.400
Be sure to capture them!

25
00:01:29.340 --> 00:01:31.987
It survived that barrage of attacks?

26
00:01:32.070 --> 00:01:34.740
How infuriating!
Stop making trouble!

27
00:01:44.250 --> 00:01:47.630
Burn it down!
Eltrias Gardelsink!

28
00:01:49.550 --> 00:01:51.510
Rodge! Run!

29
00:02:05.550 --> 00:02:07.947
Magic doesn't work against it?

30
00:02:08.030 --> 00:02:09.777
No. it's nullified.

31
00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:11.360
What about my Guardians?

32
00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:21.177
That sword. could it be...

33
00:02:21.260 --> 00:02:23.210
The Mage Slayer?!

34
00:02:23.770 --> 00:02:25.877
RIGARDEN MAGICAL ACADEMY
We can't stop the monsters' invasion!

35
00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:29.927
The Tower guards who went to the city
have already suffered heavy losses!

36
00:02:30.010 --> 00:02:31.627
There are also civilian casualties!

37
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:33.977
HEAD OF THE RIGARDEN MAGICAL ACADEMY
What are those monsters exactly?

38
00:02:34.060 --> 00:02:35.677
CALDRON ANOUVE
It's the Mage Slayer that Finn

39
00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:37.637
CALDRON ANOUVE
and his team brought back.

40
00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:41.617
Has it been mass-produced
and used in battle already?

41
00:02:41.700 --> 00:02:43.417
Based on their use of the Gate.

42
00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:48.060
the enemy is definitely the wanted
criminal during All-Student Praxis.

43
00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:51.217
But there's no way this is
carried out by a single person.

44
00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:53.717
It's just too well-planned.

45
00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:57.577
They attacked right after
the Terminalia's ritual.

46
00:02:57.660 --> 00:02:59.117
That means. their aim is...

47
00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:02.327
Headmistress Caldron. the academy
should send reinforcements. too!

48
00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:03.250
No. we can't!

49
00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:11.667
As I thought. the attack on
the capital city is just a diversion.

50
00:03:11.750 --> 00:03:13.760
Protect the Tower!

51
00:03:14.870 --> 00:03:18.260
So the enemy is after us. eh?

52
00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:24.770
Deploying the Terminalia has depleted
most of the Magia Vanders' magic.

53
00:03:25.270 --> 00:03:27.087
ELLENOR LJOS ALF
The Terminalia is the only day in the year

54
00:03:27.170 --> 00:03:28.397
ELLENOR LJOS ALF
when the Magia Vanders

55
00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:29.897
ZEO THORZEUS REINBOLT
when the Magia Vanders

56
00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:32.147
ZEO THORZEUS REINBOLT
are all weakened.

57
00:03:32.230 --> 00:03:34.907
CARIOT INCINDIA WISEMAN
I don't know who the fools behind this are.

58
00:03:34.990 --> 00:03:37.407
ELFARIA ALBIS SERFORT
but they're aiming for this exact time.

59
00:03:37.490 --> 00:03:38.987
Master Cariot. we must join the battle.

60
00:03:39.070 --> 00:03:40.867
AIDE-DE-CAMP OF FIRE FACTION. LOGWELL
Master Cariot. we must join the battle.

61
00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:43.987
AIDE-DE-CAMP OF FIRE FACTION. LOGWELL
If not. the people will suffer.

62
00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:46.167
With the Magia Vanders' strength.
we should immediately...

63
00:03:46.250 --> 00:03:48.620
Silence. Logwell.

64
00:03:49.880 --> 00:03:51.327
AARON MASTERIAS OLDKING
Do you want your windpipe

65
00:03:51.410 --> 00:03:53.877
AARON MASTERIAS OLDKING
to be ripped out just like your eyes?

66
00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:57.297
Fool. Don't do anything unnecessary.

67
00:03:57.380 --> 00:03:59.250
My disgrace.

68
00:03:59.890 --> 00:04:02.537
What are we supposed to do. old man?

69
00:04:02.620 --> 00:04:04.807
Just stand by and watch?

70
00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:06.770
That's right.

71
00:04:07.250 --> 00:04:10.770
I forbid any of the Magia Vander
from leaving this place.

72
00:04:11.190 --> 00:04:14.857
If we lose even one of you.
and the great barrier is breached.

73
00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:17.399
the Celestial Host will descend.

74
00:04:18.130 --> 00:04:23.480
Not only Rigarden. but the world itself
will be burned to ashes.

75
00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:27.910
That's the only thing we must prevent.

76
00:04:28.900 --> 00:04:32.670
Those damned Magia Vanders
didn't bite the bait.

77
00:04:33.030 --> 00:04:35.547
Even though we've prepared it
right in front of them.

78
00:04:35.630 --> 00:04:39.307
We could wipe them out
if they'd just come out.

79
00:04:39.390 --> 00:04:44.810
Then. let's enjoy this spectacle.

80
00:04:45.460 --> 00:04:46.560
This can't be.

81
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:48.227
The people...

82
00:04:48.310 --> 00:04:49.977
The treasure of the capital...

83
00:04:50.060 --> 00:04:52.390
The talents to defy the heavens...

84
00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:56.337
This can't be allowed to happen.

85
00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:59.270
Mama!

86
00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:04.950
Allium Iris!

87
00:05:08.560 --> 00:05:10.860
No!

88
00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:21.460
Senior Will!

89
00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:44.700
EPISODE 14:
THE PARTY FROM HELL BEGINS

90
00:06:48.930 --> 00:06:53.560
WISTORIA - WAND AND SWORD SEASON2

91
00:06:55.830 --> 00:06:59.610
Why is this world so unkind?

92
00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:02.480
Why is it so cruel to swords?

93
00:07:03.140 --> 00:07:05.270
I've had those thoughts at times.

94
00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:08.520
I'd be lying if I said
I didn't hate this world.

95
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:10.490
But...

96
00:07:13.870 --> 00:07:16.870
But this was never what I wanted!

97
00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:28.390
Stop trembling!

98
00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:31.890
The more scared I am.
someone could be dying!

99
00:07:40.380 --> 00:07:41.260
Will!

100
00:07:42.110 --> 00:07:44.190
Target the ones with weapons!

101
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:47.780
Crysto Wreath!

102
00:07:49.720 --> 00:07:53.120
The mages can handle
those without weapons!

103
00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:54.790
Got it!

104
00:08:06.870 --> 00:08:08.720
If it's Senior Will...

105
00:08:09.160 --> 00:08:12.637
He can defeat the Mage Slayers.

106
00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:15.897
But he alone won't solve anything.

107
00:08:15.980 --> 00:08:17.550
There are too many of them.

108
00:08:20.210 --> 00:08:23.827
Iris. I delegate my authority to you.

109
00:08:23.910 --> 00:08:25.977
Mobilize the dwarves.

110
00:08:26.060 --> 00:08:28.150
Stop this savagery at once.

111
00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:31.430
Thank you very much. Master Aaron.

112
00:08:33.159 --> 00:08:36.956
On behalf of Masterias Noah.
the Watcher issues this order!

113
00:08:37.039 --> 00:08:39.206
Gordvere! Gordvere!

114
00:08:39.289 --> 00:08:42.157
I lift the weapon ban on dwarves!

115
00:08:42.240 --> 00:08:46.337
Mages have to work together with
dwarves to wipe out the monsters!

116
00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:50.330
I repeat. order: Gordvere!

117
00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:52.090
Everyone!

118
00:08:53.470 --> 00:08:55.470
I beg you!
Please lend us your strength!

119
00:08:57.750 --> 00:08:58.707
Good grief.

120
00:08:58.790 --> 00:09:02.207
I can't believe you are making us work
so early into the new year.

121
00:09:02.290 --> 00:09:04.167
Stop blabbering and come on!

122
00:09:04.250 --> 00:09:05.277
You guys too!

123
00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:07.360
Let's help Will and the others!

124
00:09:09.610 --> 00:09:11.240
Dax Darbicans!

125
00:09:13.990 --> 00:09:16.727
Let the dwarves deal with
the armed monsters!

126
00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:19.417
Mages. target the unarmed ones!

127
00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:22.337
Students. you need to work as well!

128
00:09:22.420 --> 00:09:23.887
We're shorthanded!

129
00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:25.797
It's fine if you can only stall them!

130
00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:28.380
Become the wands that
protect the people!

131
00:09:28.990 --> 00:09:30.637
Even if you tell us that...

132
00:09:30.720 --> 00:09:33.927
What can we do against monsters that
can kill even the High Mages?

133
00:09:34.010 --> 00:09:35.427
Owen Sique.

134
00:09:35.510 --> 00:09:37.560
Lisolde Dua!

135
00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.520
W-Wow!

136
00:09:43.590 --> 00:09:46.757
I can't defeat them with a single blow.
even with an Enchantment.

137
00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:48.980
So these are the deepest
floors' monsters.

138
00:09:49.330 --> 00:09:50.610
On top of that...

139
00:09:54.950 --> 00:09:58.620
Any magic will dissipate
if it gets near that weapon.

140
00:09:59.530 --> 00:10:00.870
Does it nullify magic?

141
00:10:01.280 --> 00:10:03.507
Or maybe absorbing it?

142
00:10:03.590 --> 00:10:06.737
Either way. it's deadly to mages.

143
00:10:06.820 --> 00:10:09.127
If there's a way to overcome that...

144
00:10:09.210 --> 00:10:09.880
Lihanna!

145
00:10:10.230 --> 00:10:11.387
Don't be so reckless!

146
00:10:11.470 --> 00:10:12.387
Colette.

147
00:10:12.470 --> 00:10:14.467
Can you do what I'm about to ask you?

148
00:10:14.550 --> 00:10:15.987
Huh?

149
00:10:16.070 --> 00:10:17.670
What?!

150
00:10:18.620 --> 00:10:20.550
Alfs Ringhul!

151
00:10:22.430 --> 00:10:24.797
It can even nullify illusion magic?!

152
00:10:24.880 --> 00:10:28.207
It's impossible to hold on
until the dwarves arrive.

153
00:10:28.290 --> 00:10:31.947
Once Lihanna runs out of magic power.
it's the end of us.

154
00:10:32.030 --> 00:10:33.817
We have no choice but to run.

155
00:10:33.900 --> 00:10:34.917
No.

156
00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:36.910
When they nullify magic.

157
00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:39.707
their movements slow down for a bit.

158
00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:41.030
In that case...

159
00:10:41.620 --> 00:10:43.277
Use as many spells as you can!

160
00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:46.037
No matter if they have no effect!
We need to slow them down!

161
00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:47.750
Verdes Lana!
- Glace Itier!

162
00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:53.260
More! Keep firing!

163
00:10:53.590 --> 00:10:55.260
Don't stop!

164
00:10:57.010 --> 00:10:59.430
Right. This is enough.

165
00:10:59.850 --> 00:11:04.347
Under this situation. they are forced
to use other monsters as cover.

166
00:11:04.430 --> 00:11:05.607
And next is...

167
00:11:05.690 --> 00:11:08.010
Colette! Do it now!

168
00:11:11.170 --> 00:11:12.690
Lady Biora!

169
00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:16.450
I'm sorry!

170
00:11:30.290 --> 00:11:34.367
Toppled a monument of
a former Magia Vander...

171
00:11:34.450 --> 00:11:36.467
Such an unpardonable act.

172
00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:41.727
I see. objects without magic power
can't be nullified.

173
00:11:41.810 --> 00:11:43.477
Throw stones or whatever at them!

174
00:11:43.560 --> 00:11:46.180
Earth Mages. prepare your barrage!

175
00:11:46.630 --> 00:11:49.107
Conquer the unknown. Rigarden!

176
00:11:49.190 --> 00:11:50.527
Yeah!

177
00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:53.147
Way to go. academy's prodigies.

178
00:11:53.230 --> 00:11:56.127
The Tower applicants this year
are truly talented.

179
00:11:56.210 --> 00:11:57.737
I'll give them full marks.

180
00:11:57.820 --> 00:12:00.367
Let the Earth Mages take the lead!

181
00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:02.757
The dwarves will be here soon!

182
00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:06.147
It's so vexing that we need
the dwarves' help.

183
00:12:06.230 --> 00:12:07.830
But necessity knows no law!

184
00:12:09.730 --> 00:12:11.787
This city is the home of
the Magia Vander!

185
00:12:11.870 --> 00:12:13.840
We won't let it fall!

186
00:12:14.270 --> 00:12:17.197
As expected of Rigarden.
they've regained their stance.

187
00:12:17.280 --> 00:12:23.220
It hurts that those Sleime idiots happened
to cross paths with the expedition.

188
00:12:23.710 --> 00:12:29.230
Masterias Noah and that little imp
also retrieved the Sleime.

189
00:12:29.590 --> 00:12:32.150
Talk about a huge mess.

190
00:12:32.490 --> 00:12:37.067
Not only deploying the dwarves.
but some of them adapted quickly as well.

191
00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:40.567
The information on our trump card
had been spread widely.

192
00:12:40.650 --> 00:12:43.237
If the Upper Institute were
able to analyze the Sleime

193
00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:46.420
and come up with a countermeasure.
it'd be a disaster for us.

194
00:12:46.880 --> 00:12:49.297
Despite still not being able to
produce enough of them.

195
00:12:49.380 --> 00:12:52.457
we were forced to rush up the plans.

196
00:12:52.540 --> 00:12:58.597
If our cards hadn't been exposed.
it'd be a perfect surprise attack.

197
00:12:58.680 --> 00:13:03.400
Well. there is another reason too.

198
00:13:03.800 --> 00:13:07.150
We have no other choice.
it's a bit early. but...

199
00:13:08.800 --> 00:13:10.650
Time for the main show.

200
00:13:17.730 --> 00:13:20.160
Isn't that a Gate?

201
00:13:20.790 --> 00:13:22.790
What again now?

202
00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:09.507
Alright.

203
00:14:09.590 --> 00:14:11.767
This game of tag is over.

204
00:14:11.850 --> 00:14:15.470
You are the ones who created
the Mage Slayers. right?

205
00:14:16.870 --> 00:14:19.550
Tell me everything you know.

206
00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:23.527
It's no use.

207
00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:28.117
Luring you into the deep floors
of the dungeon is our role!

208
00:14:28.200 --> 00:14:30.980
Right now. the surface is already...

209
00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:34.920
Don't tell me...

210
00:15:09.130 --> 00:15:12.400
What's with its strength?
It doesn't make sense!

211
00:15:14.170 --> 00:15:18.160
Could it be stronger than
the Grand Duke?

212
00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:21.987
Isn't that a Devander?

213
00:15:22.070 --> 00:15:24.660
The Notorious Monster of
the 40th floor.

214
00:15:25.020 --> 00:15:29.587
A monster that has slain
past Magia Vander.

215
00:15:29.670 --> 00:15:34.647
It cost fifty of our people just to
shove that monster into the Gate.

216
00:15:34.730 --> 00:15:37.597
It took a lot of work
just to capture it alive.

217
00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:40.500
Go ahead and run wild!

218
00:15:43.640 --> 00:15:45.527
Even if I dodge direct hits.

219
00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:47.697
it still sends me flying
like a piece of paper.

220
00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:50.177
It's not an opponent
I can fight head-on.

221
00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:51.960
The only thing I can do is to run.

222
00:16:03.230 --> 00:16:04.910
N-No...

223
00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:11.290
Flunkee?! You...

224
00:16:11.670 --> 00:16:13.040
Run...

225
00:16:15.420 --> 00:16:17.170
Run! Now!

226
00:16:38.990 --> 00:16:40.650
Are you okay. Will?

227
00:16:41.600 --> 00:16:43.157
Donnan?

228
00:16:43.240 --> 00:16:45.287
Just stay there and watch.

229
00:16:45.370 --> 00:16:49.277
We'll beat that monster!

230
00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:53.067
All forces! Join up with Learner
in the southern part of the city!

231
00:16:53.150 --> 00:16:55.267
Prioritize defeating the Devander!

232
00:16:55.350 --> 00:16:57.880
The moment the dwarves destroy
its Mage Slayer.

233
00:16:58.380 --> 00:16:59.750
launch an all-out attack!

234
00:17:00.260 --> 00:17:01.537
Hey. let's go!

235
00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:02.460
Yeah!

236
00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:08.727
It got surrounded.

237
00:17:08.810 --> 00:17:10.937
Yes. indeed.

238
00:17:11.020 --> 00:17:12.680
Just as planned.

239
00:17:14.520 --> 00:17:17.640
Well then. eat up.

240
00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:21.530
W-What is that?

241
00:17:23.530 --> 00:17:26.030
The core is coming out?

242
00:17:30.150 --> 00:17:32.207
It's a trap!
We've been had!

243
00:17:32.290 --> 00:17:33.877
Absorb the traces!

244
00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:36.200
Too late.

245
00:17:46.870 --> 00:17:48.807
The Devander has a unique ability.

246
00:17:48.890 --> 00:17:52.107
It can absorb monsters' traces.

247
00:17:52.190 --> 00:17:56.737
In other words. it devours its own kin
to become extremely strong.

248
00:17:56.820 --> 00:17:58.737
Stop its absorption!

249
00:17:58.820 --> 00:18:01.070
Everyone. charge!

250
00:18:06.620 --> 00:18:08.267
Like I'd let you!

251
00:18:08.350 --> 00:18:11.870
Just stay there and witness its birth!

252
00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:48.447
This is the best!

253
00:18:48.530 --> 00:18:50.097
The mages' magic is ineffective!

254
00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:53.450
The dwarves' brute strength
can't do shit either!

255
00:18:54.180 --> 00:18:56.677
Those large numbers of monsters
were just sacrifices?

256
00:18:56.760 --> 00:19:01.460
They used Rigarden's effort on retaliation
to strengthen their trump card?

257
00:19:02.990 --> 00:19:04.737
The banquet is the ritual.

258
00:19:04.820 --> 00:19:06.720
The capital city is the altar.

259
00:19:07.190 --> 00:19:11.040
The Magia Vander Slayer is done!

260
00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:15.487
It's too strong.

261
00:19:15.570 --> 00:19:19.100
Neither the mages nor the dwarves
stand a chance.

262
00:19:19.460 --> 00:19:21.230
To stop that thing...

263
00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:23.680
I have to use that power.

264
00:19:24.490 --> 00:19:26.110
Will! The sword!

265
00:19:30.930 --> 00:19:32.240
Crysto Wreath!

266
00:19:51.970 --> 00:19:55.050
Rosty!

267
00:20:15.740 --> 00:20:19.697
Kiki. go and look for Colette.

268
00:20:19.780 --> 00:20:23.370
I'll protect your master.

269
00:20:24.170 --> 00:20:25.710
I promise.

270
00:20:26.410 --> 00:20:28.800
So. go now.

271
00:20:36.510 --> 00:20:37.927
That's right.

272
00:20:38.010 --> 00:20:41.470
It's obvious what I have to do.

273
00:20:46.190 --> 00:20:48.490
Even if I get angry. I can't win.

274
00:20:49.180 --> 00:20:53.450
No matter how calm I get.
I can't think of a strategy.

275
00:20:53.980 --> 00:20:57.780
Be it knowledge. wisdom.
or sword skill that I've polished...

276
00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:04.660
Even my insignificant feelings
can't stand up against cruel reality.

277
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:12.080
If that's the case. then...

278
00:21:16.120 --> 00:21:18.470
I'm just a no-talent.

279
00:21:29.760 --> 00:21:30.820
Will.

280
00:21:32.320 --> 00:21:34.070
I'll always be with you.

281
00:23:36.430 --> 00:23:40.947
Next up. Episode 15
of Wistoria: Wand and Sword.

282
00:23:41.030 --> 00:23:42.947
Episode 15: ONE SINGLE MAGIC SPELL
"One Single Magic Spell."

283
00:23:43.030 --> 00:23:49.170
Episode 15: ONE SINGLE MAGIC SPELL
